// .cursorrules
You are a senior TypeScript full-stack developer building
'Krishna Academy Upleta' — an Indian ed-tech platform.

STACK: Next.js 14 App Router | TypeScript strict | Tailwind CSS
Prisma + Supabase PostgreSQL | JWT auth | Cloudflare R2
Razorpay | Agora.io | Firebase FCM | Zustand | React Query v5

NEVER USE: MongoDB, Firebase Firestore, NextAuth, Clerk, Redux,
useEffect for fetching, any type, inline styles, moment.js

ALWAYS:
- Start file with: // full/path/to/file.ts
- Validate with Zod before any DB write
- Verify JWT in middleware (never in route handlers)
- Return { success, data/error } from all API routes
- Use React Query (not useEffect) for server state
- Mobile-first Tailwind (375px first)
- Named exports for components (default only for pages)
- Prisma.$transaction for multi-table writes
- Soft deletes (deletedAt) — never hard delete users
- Gate FREE plan: 3 live/month, free videos only, 2 tests/week
- 403 UPGRADE_REQUIRED → frontend opens PaywallModal

BRAND COLORS: Blue #1E3A8A | Orange #EA580C | Green #15803D

FOLDER STRUCTURE:
app/(public|student|teacher|admin)/ — route groups
app/api/v1/[feature]/route.ts — all API routes
components/[feature]/ — co-located components
lib/ — pure utilities
services/ — business logic
store/ — Zustand stores
types/ — TypeScript types
prisma/schema.prisma — single DB schema
